        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 12:01PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 1200 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southeast of Lake City, or 45 miles south of Gunnison, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation and
outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central
Hinsdale County.

This includes Colorado 149 between mile markers 43 and 56.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
